   "mechanism": "On days with no scheduled macro release (no FOMC/CPI on the calendar), intraday price movement is driven by inventory and order-flow imbalance rather than information, so the first-60-minute directional displacement reflects a liquidity-provider inventory imbalance that must keep being paid for through the rest of the session; on scheduled-event days an information shock resets order books and kills that persistence, so the edge should only appear when the macro calendar is empty.",
