  "mes-funding-basis-stress-cheapening": {
   "name": "mes-funding-basis-stress-cheapening",
   "market": "MES",
   "tier": "candidate",
   "mechanism": "Index futures embed an implicit dealer financing/collateral leg (Baltussen, Terstegge & Whelan, \"The Derivative Payoff Bias\"); when dealer balance-sheet capacity is most constrained around calendar quarter-end regulatory reporting dates, repo/collateral funding is pulled from cash-futures basis arbitrageurs, transiently cheapening MES futures against fair value into the quarter-end and re-converging (richening back up) in the first sessions of the new quarter. The buyer of the cheapened future during the reversal leg is paid a balance-sheet-rental fee, not a directional forecast.",
